trans-unit.source: Encapsulates the collection of <xref href="System.Drawing.Image"></xref> objects in an <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref>.
This is used to manage the images in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList> programmatically, providing methods to add and remove image objects.
Adds the specified icon to the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref>.
The <xref:System.Drawing.Icon> is converted to a <xref:System.Drawing.Bitmap> before it is added to the list.
An <xref href="System.Drawing.Icon"></xref> to add to the list.
value is `null`
-or-
value is not an <xref href="System.Drawing.Icon"></xref>.
Adds the specified image to the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref>.
A <xref href="System.Drawing.Bitmap"></xref> of the image to add to the list.
The image being added is `null`.
The image being added is not a <xref href="System.Drawing.Bitmap"></xref>.
Adds the specified image to the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref>, using the specified color to generate the mask.
A <xref href="System.Drawing.Bitmap"></xref> of the image to add to the list.
The <xref href="System.Drawing.Color"></xref> to mask this image.
The index of the newly added image, or -1 if the image cannot be added.
The image being added is `null`.
The image being added is not a <xref href="System.Drawing.Bitmap"></xref>.
Adds an icon with the specified key to the end of the collection.
The name of an image corresponds to its key in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection>.
An image key is not case-sensitive.
The name of the icon.
The <xref href="System.Drawing.Icon"></xref> to add to the collection.
icon is `null`.
Adds an image with the specified key to the end of the collection.
The name of an image corresponds to its key in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection>.
An image key is not case-sensitive.
The name of the image.
The <xref href="System.Drawing.Image"></xref> to add to the collection.
image is `null`.
Adds an array of images to the collection.
Use <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection> to add several images to the collection.
To add a single item, use one of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Add%2A> methods.
The array of <xref href="System.Drawing.Image"></xref> objects to add to the collection.
images is `null`.
Adds an image strip for the specified image to the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref>.
The number of images to add is inferred from the width of the given image.
A strip is a single image that is treated as multiple images arranged side-by-side.
A <xref href="System.Drawing.Bitmap"></xref> with the images to add.
The index of the newly added image, or -1 if the image cannot be added.
The image being added is `null`.
-or-
The image being added is not a <xref href="System.Drawing.Bitmap"></xref>.
The image cannot be added.
-or-
The width of image strip being added is 0, or the width is not equal to the existing image width.
-or-
The image strip height is not equal to existing image height.
Removes all the images and masks from the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref>.
Not supported.
The <xref href="System.Collections.IList.Contains(System.Object)"></xref> method indicates whether a specified object is contained in the list.
This implementation of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Contains%2A> method throws a <xref:System.NotSupportedException> exception.
The <xref href="System.Drawing.Image"></xref> to find in the list.
`true` if the image is found in the list; otherwise, `false`.
This method is not supported.
Determines if the collection contains an image with the specified key.
The name of an image corresponds to its key.
The key comparison is not case-sensitive.
If the `key` parameter is `null` or an empty string, the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.ContainsKey%2A> method returns `false`.
The key of the image to search for.
`true` to indicate an image with the specified key is contained in the collection; otherwise, `false`.
Gets the number of images currently in the list.
Counting the images forces the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.Handle%2A> to be created.
The number of images in the list.
The default is 0.
Gets a value indicating whether the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref> has any images.
You can check this property without forcing the creation of a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.Handle%2A>.
`true` if there are no images in the list; otherwise, `false`.
The default is `false`.
Returns an enumerator that can be used to iterate through the item collection.
An <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> that represents the item collection.
Not supported.
The <xref href="System.Collections.IList.IndexOf(System.Object)"></xref> method returns the index of a specified object in the list.
This implementation of <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.IndexOf%2A> throws a <xref:System.NotSupportedException> exception.
The <xref href="System.Drawing.Image"></xref> to find in the list.
The index of the image in the list.
This method is not supported.
Determines the index of the first occurrence of an image with the specified key in the collection.

If <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.IndexOfKey%2A> is called successively, the last returned index will be checked for a key match first, and if there is no match, the search starts at the beginning of the collection.
The name of an image corresponds to its key in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection>.
The key comparison is not case-sensitive.
If the `key` parameter is `null` or an empty string, the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.IndexOfKey%2A> method returns -1.
The key of the image to retrieve the index for.
The zero-based index of the first occurrence of an image with the specified key in the collection, if found; otherwise, -1.
Gets a value indicating whether the list is read-only.
Always `false`.
Gets an <xref href="System.Drawing.Image"></xref> with the specified key from the collection.
The name of an image corresponds to its key in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection>.
The key comparison is not case-sensitive.
If an image with the specified key is not found, the value of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Item%2A> property is `null`.
The name of the image to retrieve from the collection.
The <xref href="System.Drawing.Image"></xref> with the specified key.
Gets or sets an <xref href="System.Drawing.Image"></xref> at the specified index within the collection.
The returned bitmap is a copy of the original image and should be disposed of using the <xref:System.Drawing.Image.Dispose%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method.
The index of the image to get or set.
The image in the list specified by index.
The index is less than 0 or greater than or equal to <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Count"></xref>.
image is not a .
The image to be assigned is `null` or not a <xref href="System.Drawing.Bitmap"></xref>.
The image cannot be added to the list.
Gets the collection of keys associated with the images in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection"></xref>.
The name of an image corresponds to its key, and an image key is not case-sensitive.

If none of the images contained in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection> have keys, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Keys%2A> returns an empty <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringCollection>.
A <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringCollection"></xref> containing the names of the images in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection"></xref>.
Not supported.
The <xref href="System.Collections.IList.Remove(System.Object)"></xref> method removes a specified object from the list.
This implementation of <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Remove%2A> throws a <xref:System.NotSupportedException> exception.
The <xref href="System.Drawing.Image"></xref> to remove from the list.
This method is not supported.
Removes an image from the list.
The index of the image to remove.
The image cannot be removed.
The index value was less than 0.
-or-
The index value is greater than or equal to the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Count"></xref> of images.
Removes the image with the specified key from the collection.
The key comparison is not case-sensitive.
The name of an image corresponds to its key in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection>.
The key of the image to remove from the collection.
Sets the key for an image in the collection.
The name of an image corresponds to its key in the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection>.
An image key is not case-sensitive.
The zero-based index of an image in the collection.
The name of the image to be set as the image key.
The specified index is less than 0 or greater than or equal to <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Count"></xref>.
Copies the items in this collection to a compatible one-dimensional array, starting at the specified index of the target array.
The one-dimensional <xref href="System.Array"></xref> that is the destination of the elements copied from the collection.
The array must have zero-based indexing.
The zero-based index in the <xref href="System.Array"></xref> at which copying begins.
dest is `null`.
index is less than 0.
dest is multidimensional.
-or-
The number of elements in the is greater than the available space from index to the end of the destination array.
The type of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ComboBox.ObjectCollection"></xref> cannot be cast automatically to the type of the destination array.
Gets a value indicating whether access to the collection is synchronized (thread safe).
`false` in all cases.
Gets an object that can be used to synchronize access to the collection.
The object used to synchronize the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection"></xref>.
Adds the specified image to the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref>.
The image to add to the list.
The index of the newly added image, or -1 if the image could not be added.
value is `null`.
value is not a .
Implements the <xref href="System.Collections.IList.Contains(System.Object)"></xref> method.
Throws a <xref href="System.NotSupportedException"></xref> in all cases.
The image to locate in the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection"></xref>.
In all cases.
Implements the <xref href="System.Collections.IList.IndexOf(System.Object)"></xref> method.
Throws a <xref href="System.NotSupportedException"></xref> in all cases.
The image to find in the list.
In all cases.
Implements the <xref href="System.Collections.IList.Insert(System.Int32,System.Object)"></xref> method.
Throws a <xref href="System.NotSupportedException"></xref> in all cases.
To add an item to the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection>, use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ImageList.ImageCollection.Add%2A> method.
The zero-based index at which value should be inserted.
The object to insert into the collection.
In all cases.

`false` in all cases.
